comment:
Is Amber Heard, related to Jack Heard, well known former police officer?   I used to work for him when he owned a security company called "GuardEx, which later changed to GuardCo".
Excerpt from lawsuit:
"The Government alleged that over the course of eighteen years, Heard, Lambert, and other defendants conspired to defraud the United States out of millions of dollars in employment taxes withheld by Heard's security companies. Overall, the Government alleges that the companies failed to pay a substantial sum in employment taxes, totaling over $5 million."

Source:
https://caselaw.findlaw.com/us-5th-circuit/1623688.html

I'll share an interesting story with ya, about a particular time when I was working as a security guard.  It was near Christmas time, all the lights were up, and I was,  around 17 ta 20 years old at the time, being 50 years old now.

They asked me if I would work a shift at a particular location, they told me not to worry, cause nothing ever happens there, and I had access to a golf cart for transportation.  They told me not to let the cart run out of juice, and that I would be working with "big guys", driving black surburban's, not sure what law enforcement agency they were with.   Sheriff's Department, I believe.  I sat in his car, he beat around the bush asking me some questions, was real polite, then I got out and got into my golf cart, he drove away, and not long after that's when the alarms started going off.

I went around the back, and saw the door had been tampered with, and that's when I got on the horn as per regulations, to contact my superior, and he would contact the cops.

Being non-commissioned, I wasn't there to stop crimes from happening, but to observe, and communicate, without engagment.

The funny part about the whole deal was I let the golf cart run out of juice, and I plugged it into the nearest outlet where they had all the Christmas lights plugged into, and it blew out all the lights hanging on the tree's.

On another occassion, I had my paycheck stoken from whom I suspected was my superior!  Didn't get a replacement till some weeks later after a lot of harrassment.

Another time I was stationed at Gillman Honda, first working in the garage, then at the "Finish Gate" checking trunks, and logging VIN numbers making sure employee's wern't stealing car radios, etc.   Come to find out, some of the security guards were stealing them.

I was in love, had a great crush on Stacy Gillman, and drew with my fingers on the cars "I (heart) Stacy Gillman" all over the windshields.   In the morning, when the sun started to rise, and my shift was over, I could see the effects of my work, and I'll tell ya, I gut cussed out big time by my superior, "You ever pull that @#$!@$ again, I'll see to it you never work another security job, blah blah blah!"

Love sure does hurt, when it's not mutual!

Someone probably told her some crazy skinny as a tooth pick security guard was in love with her.  I wouldn't doubt it.  Hardly ever do the upper class fall in love with us peasants.

I think she's a psychopath. NPD doesn't fit because they usually can't admit to harming a person unless they think it was for their own good, even then they can't admit it in the same way. The callousness, the "no one will believe you" and just how violent she was indicates possible psychopathy. 

Psychopaths are constantly bored. Their brain didn't fully develop in a lot of areas and as a consequence they don't see other people, they see tools and toys. Johnny for her was both. They also have a higher propensity for a violent streak. Some don't become killers, they just become this instead and tend to be in places of power.
A possible detection would be to see if she has a disgust response or can read it on others. That part of the brain doesn't function well in psychopaths, which is why quite a few that end up as serial killers do some really nasty things that are actually dangerous to their own health as well. 
Psychopaths also tend to have lower IQ than the average person, even though hollywood perpetuates the notion that they are secret geniuses, they are really not. They make bad impulsive decisions all the time, especially because they are bored.

I wonder what she was like to work with on sets? Psychopaths are also known for being charming and good at manipulation.

This would also explain why her parents came forth and defended Johnny. Psychopaths are born that way, where as NPD seems to be a combination of abuse and genetic propensity, psychopaths show signs as early as 3 years old. Her parents may of seen early signs of manipulation.

A really big obvious flag is animal abuse/torture in youth. It's so common that it's a trope for psychopaths.

comment: I married a women who has BPD.  She was mentally and physically abusive then convinced members of my family and her co-workers that it was me who was being abusive.  In the end she did me a favor as she exposed people in my life whom I believed that I was close to.  She later apologized for her behavior.  I am not sure her motive for apologizing. Perhaps it was even sincere.  Like her compliments and abuse I learned early on  not  to read too much into the face-value of her words. She was incredibly intelligent, attractive and when when I was the "greatest guy in the world" she was fiercely loyal.  The problem is that it only takes a flip of a switch(in her brain, I guess) and suddenly you are "the worst guy in the world".  I fell in love with her.  Several months in I saw my first real sign and I ignored it.  It changed my ability to open up with her but I mostly ignored it and hoped that it would get better.  It never got better.  I was already in my mid-late 30's  when we met and pretty secure about who  I was as a person...had she gotten ahold of me when I was a 15-20 years younger she could have easily destroyed me.  They toy with your self worth.  Either trying to build you to great heights with their flattery or tearing you to the ground with their vicious words  or fits of physical violence.  If this is true of Amber I understand why Johnny was afraid.  My wife was very good at pretending ..only people who knew her well could tell that it was all an act.  She told me after several years of us being apart (and her apology)that "she didn't choose to be that way"...It does not absolve her of responsibility of her actions but I realized that she is correct.  It is an illness.  It is an illness that is as destructive to the people around the inflicted person as it is to the one who is inflicted.  I feel for anyone who is currently  living in this situation.  If the person is not willing to seek help then get out. comment:
She gives us women who have actually been strangled stalked raped etc. a bad name.  The ones telling the truth.  We want to scream that we would never make these things up and ruin the life of another human. That we are only telling our stories hoping to be believed for the future safety of the daughters of others.  Even when we have all the proof some of us still hope to merely be believed.   Fortunately for me, my case is moving forward since the jurors voted together last month that they all believe what happened
to me.  The next court date is all the way in October, so once again I will just tell my truth and let God universe ultimately be the judge.  This person was my ex-boyfriend ( I‚Äôm embarrassed to admit I was ever with) and then stalker and rapist (still feels so very weird and victim using that word but that is what he is.) In the same bedroom as my sleeping toddler after breaking into my parents‚Äô house.  I didn‚Äôt want to scream and wake her and tried with everything I had to get away and just physically couldn‚Äôt.  I had to play it cool to get him out of the room when he was done.  He insisted I wouldn‚Äôt get pregnant and showed my my cycle on his phone.  Disgusting.  He got out of the house FINALLY when I found my phone which he moved while I was sleeping.  He stood at the bottom of the stairs and figured that I must have been starting to dial for help.  I looked up and he was gone.  I wondered if he was hiding somewhere in the house
still.  I had to to a super fun rape kit at the hospital around 4 am. Needless to say I still took plan B after.  He bailed himself out at over 41,000 something and is currently roaming freely- probably somewhere in So Cal, in the LA area where his family is.  He actually wrote a published book years ago called The Treasures of Divine Love.. oh the irony.  That SAID üòÖ my heart goes out to the truthful men falsely accused by women only seeking attention in the sickest of ways.  What those like Depp need more than anything is sobriety so they can find peace, see people more clearly find real love.  I tell my story to show that there really are people out there who are dangerous.  And I would rather say what happened to me than be ashamed or feel like it should be a secret.  Life is too short and people need to be aware of the warning signs.  What I was missing was self-love.  I was a tired, scared, lonely suddenly single mom without child support in a new state that my parents moved to.  If I at least had healthy boundaries, I would have never dated that person and would have
gotten a restraining order fast.  I would have seen him for who he really was in the very beginning.  EMDR therapy has helped me exponentially.  I am  a 2015 university grad so I have some book smarts, but clearly needed to work on my street smarts and I still am. Signs I hope and pray to teach my daughter well

comment:
It‚Äôs been proven that the violent events, as Amber described them, were ‚Äúsubstantially true‚Äù in a court of law. I don‚Äôt understand why people are backing Jonny Depp‚Äôs version of events still.

The burden of proof lies with the accused in a libel case, which means in order to get this verdict the newspapers had to prove that what Amber had said was true, the burden of proof was not on Johnny Depp‚Äôs team. In this scenario the newspapers settle outside of court 99% of the time. They didn‚Äôt in this case because they were so sure that Jonny Depp committed ‚Äúunprovoked acts of violence that put Amber Heard in fear of her life‚Äù. It is almost unprecedented. He is a wife beater. 

Since this verdict there has been an incredible amount of rhetoric about ‚Äúcrazy Amber‚Äù intimating that she is making it up. She is not. It has been proven that what she is saying is ‚Äúsubstantially true‚Äù. 

I can‚Äôt help but think this is the same deplorable cowardice that leads to someone saying ‚Äúwell she was probably asking for it wearing that dress‚Äù

I don‚Äôt understand, we haven‚Äôt moved on one step with ‚Äúme too‚Äù, it‚Äôs all for nothing if this continues. You are staring legal evidence in the face and just ignoring it to protect a man you love for some shit pirate movie

comment:
I have followed this case for some time now and have seen the court documents and the evidence presented. There is  no doubt in my mind at all that Amber Heard is not only the abuser in this case, but a blatant liar and shameless manipulator.
But no-one should take anyones word for that. Go and review the evidence and the facts of the case available and make up your own mind. 
It's so vitally important in this time of hearsay and media bias and dishonesty, to be able to access facts and evidence so you can determine their credibility for yourself.
The channels that I follow and  know to be covering this case in depth, going over evidence and court documents, are the following: 

Lost Beyond Pluto    (she is a lawyer and goes through the court documents and the case from a law perspective -very informative)
ThatUmbrellaGuy    (Great content, always directly backed by the latest evidence)
Stevie J Raw     (also absolutely excellent at going through the evidence and facts - has full readings of witness and defence statements)
Come Geek Some    (same, references and goes over facts and court documents)
Colonel Kurtz     (has very interesting in-depth content on the case from a more psychological/philosophical angle)

As mentioned, Stevie J Raw has uploaded FULL unedited readings of the court statements of Amber Heard, Johnny Depp and other important key persons in the case, giving you direct access to their own statements so you can compare and come up with your own opinion as to who is telling the truth.

comment:
I really want to see this woman held to task for what she has done.
I myself am a victim of domestic abuse at the hands of a woman, and I have seen how these things go first hand. The fact that SO many people are leaping to his defence speaks volumes.
All too often, people brush of the idea that men can be victims of domestic abuse, but it does happen. My Ex beat me black and blue regularly, I would go into work with all kinds of injuries and people would not believe me because "she was a woman" This woman broke my jaw, she strangled me to the point where even to this day, more than 9 years later, I STILL have issues with swallowing even water because of the injuries she caused me... but what happened at the time? She called the police claiming I assaulted her, even though she didn't have a mark on her anywhere and I was bleeding and bruised. I was arrested and put in jail for 24 hours. why? because I'm a man. Men are ALWAYS seen as the aggressor, no one ever believes that the woman could be the one to commit an assault. I lost my job, I lost my home, I was made homeless. I slept in the streets, in the rain, because a woman assaulted me. My life was ruined because of her. And this is exactly what Amber is doing to Johnny. She's playing the "innocent victim", "I'm just a tiny little woman" card, and people are falling for it... It makes me sick... 
It's bad enough that people like Myself, Johnny and countless other men face this abuse, but for it to get laughed at, ignored and to be called liars is so much worse. People need to realise that this is a very real issue, that this is something that DOES happen. Some women can be abusive, manipulative and cruel, just as some men can be. People cry for equality between sexes... that encompasses EVERYTHING, not what you choose.
author: MetalHead Reacts

comment: Not saying the overall conclusion is wrong but I highly doubt body language experts are going to be effective on an actor. It's kinda their job to deceive people. Plus, "body language experts" opinions tend to be unreliable; they're good at hindsight explanations but not predicting the unknown (though they are excellent at detecting POSSIBLY dangerous cues). Also, depositions can sometimes last all day long and people get hungry/tired of being stressed out for so long. It's also a common tactic to eat food or drink water to stall so you can carefully word your answers: which is VERY IMPORTANT regardless if you have the truth on your side. Also,  lawyers at that level don't care about the truth so long as their getting paid. I'm sure Amber has spent millions on the case already so it's not unreasonable for her to want to reduce costs. It could also be due to Amber being a diva or some other crazy crud. Once again, I take Depp's side in all this, I just think this video's sort of speculation is pointless.

comment: Johnny might be eccentric and he might drink/take drugs, but I think he's a decent bloke at his core. I highly doubt he's ever laid a hand on Amber with intent to harm her. Especially after hearing tapes of them arguing. She's manipulative, calculated and frankly comes off as un-empathetic. She wants to be the star of her own real life drama and deliberately creates unnecessary, irrational and over-enhanced drama as a result. The only thing I can say in her defence, is that she's perhaps bi-polar and untreated for that. But consider the clip of Johnny losing his mind when his mother passed away. Does Amber comfort him? Find out what happened? No, she's opportunistic. She sees an opening for herself to capture some raw emotion. So Amber films it, makes it all about her. 'What happened? We haven't even been fighting today?' Implying that she's just so used to instigating that as she hasn't done anything to stirr the pot yet, she is totally baffled by Johnny being bothered by something that isn't her. He slams cupboards, takes his anger and pain out on inanimate objects, pours himself a drink and presumably pushes the phone over when he realises he's being filmed. Amber laughs at him as he walks away like she's won something over him because she caught him being emotional. What does Amber do? She sends that to TMZ. Paparazzi. If that's not transparent I don't know what is. She's dug herself too deep a hole and is out of her depth. Karma will not be a fun place for her.

comment:
Yes I think Amber's accusations are a hoax. From the beginning of their relationship I figured she wanted to use Johnny for fame and money. I never considered she wanted to ruin him. When Amber claimed Johnny abused her I was leaning toward skeptical but remained neutral and kept an open mind as more proven info was released. I've seen footage of Amber being interviewed about Johnny and noticed a few signs of possible dishonesty - head nodding, eating and the bored look. I was convinced she was lying at this point but unclear to what extent. Later watched Observe's video of his analysis and he pointed out what I noticed and a  whole LOT more as well. I hate that Amber is doing such damage to the movement against domestic violence and violence/assault/harassment of women. On the other hand she is bringing attention to another unspoken topic - that women can be the abusers and men can be abused by women too. I watch a lot of ID so I've heard of such women who are abusers of men or worse. We shouldn't disbelieve someone because of their gender or age etc, everyone deserves to be heard (ugh, no pun intended) but at the same time we need to be careful with such accusations or we could condemn and ruin an innocent person's life. My nephew was dating a girl he wanted to break up with and she started telling other students at school that he either did or tried to rape or hit her after. His mother has her texts from her when she confronted the girl on the accusations and she was not at all acting like a victim. She was rude, smug and acted like it was a hilarious joke. Not how a victim behaves right? His mother called or texted the girl's father and informed him what she was doing. He was receptive and calm and apparently furious with his daughter. Things never went further than that so it seems her father dealt with her appropriately (don't know how) because I never heard any more about it. 
#Justice4Johnny
author: Elizabeth Lovett

comment: body language analysis is highly flawed. My friend is currently in law school, there are many scientists who say its's too biased and relies on faulty analysis. There is no right or wrong way for someone to behave. Many psychologists also agree its a highly flawed way to determine if someone is guilty or not because often people with anxiety, or other types of mental illness fidget and move around. Some people‚Äôs natural body language is more assertive others are not. Body language analysis is hardly ever used in court anymore because of its highly unreliable methodology. Although sometimes can be used to try and understand behaviour because different cultures, classes and genders might use body language different its not universal and can lead to people misreading a person.

comment: I too think JD will be eventually vindicated and AH found the real villain. I am not usually very interested in celebrity news per se, but there are stories that seem to come from broader human issues than typical H'wood glitz and glamor. I have followed JD in his roles  and interviews since he was on tv in Jumpstreet. I'm a fan and may seem therefore prejudiced. I also know people we like can be violent behind doors as is claimed here. Anyone victim of domestic abuse deserves support and justice. But I am very suspicious of AH. I DON'T like her bc there's something belligerent, short-fused, arrogant, fake, devious, negative, egotistical and vindictive in her bearing and overall vibe that I can't always put my finger on, which calls her character into question, and trips all my intuition's red alerts, as well as ongoing remarks and support for JD from respectable quarters that make me weigh her accusation carefully. I watch the things she says and how she says them in her many interviews.. as well as I have his. They are both actors and we have to consider that aspect of their public reactions as being professional in convincing roles. But because of this, you'd think she would be more in control of her affect that I often find suspect, and hold as evidence against her. I really believe, as time goes on, we will continue to see her proved to be untrustworthy, self serving, malicious, manipulative and unworthy of the favoring in courts that have transpired.Time will tell who is who in this saga. What is done in secret will be heard on the rooftops. Blood will out.

Yeah, those that saw her right after the "so called" attack, stated she had no injuries. Even days later, nothing. Yet photos of her "alleged" injuries and her showing up in court to get the restraining order showed her with bruising that hadn't been there before.
So either she used makeup to fake it, photo shopped the pictures or something else... it's clear it wasn't JD who caused them.
Even his kids were there on the island when she went after him & witnessed it. The manager on the island also had to put herself between to stop her from attacking him.
I believe when they were in that movie - she saw him as a mark. Someone who she could manipulate & control. She became this illusion, someone JD fell in love with. But it was only an act, it wasn't real. He fell in love with the illusion and then felt powerless to escape. She's often shown wearing heels to make her above JD's eye level so he has to look up to her. This was done mostly just before the wedding and right after it got more frequent. She would also make sure she was at a higher level so she'd be above JD. She's been recorded looking superior & smirking, enjoying her power over him. JD in comparison, looks down a lot, tries to put space between them & often is unsure about touching her till she seems to "allow" it.
When someone is abused, especially a man, it's harsh on their mental health & self confidence. He's a quiet, kind and sweet man. He turned to drink and drugs for two reasons.
One to escape the shame, pain & depression. Two, it was a silent cry for help subconsciously.
That harpy used typical verbal abuse to tear JD down... including "No one will believe you!" a classic one. I hope JD gets justice for this horrible nightmare he's had to deal with.

comment:
Johnny Depp is probably one of the most devout, theatrical, craftsman...his roles are nuanced, consistant, and so well developed. Alongside that kind of artistry comes alot of stress; my mother was an actress. After a very spot on performance, whether during rehearsal or during performance ITSELF, coming out of a strenuous character, IS STRENUOUS! ADRENALINE, CORTISOL, AND ALL TYPES OF PERFORMANCE STRESSORS CAN CAUSE DEPENDENCY ON CHEMICALS. ALCOHOL, TRANQUILIZERS, PAINKILLERS, AND EVEN PRESCRIBED MEDICATIONS,  CAN HAVE SPURIOUS, DELETERIOUS EFFECTS OVER TIME.

My son and I always enjoyed a Johnny Depp character. Does this mean I think he is innocent? Not necessarily.

What I hear when I listen to the taped conversations, is two people whose love was at one time very powerful. You might even guess that it turned into a Russian Roulette, of sorts. They are both quilty of not seeking help when the relationship became toxic and dangerous...kind of a competition between the two...sort of like, which one of us loves NOT ENOUGH OR TOO MUCH. The pain during their unfolding, devolution, devoured their ability to walk away with honor and some wisdom. Love is a dance between two humans. If they don't know how to "dance" in a true partnership/team effort, then they end up injuring each other and unable to get out of their own way.

I am not as familiar with Ms. Heard's craftsmanship. She is a great beauty, for sure. That comes with its own set of problems. Her assertions that no one would believe Johnny do indicate a level of premeditation or some planning towards "winning" this ugly battle between them. No one wins in these situations, nor should they. I do think the "cut me" remarks by Mr. Depp allude to his desperation as a human to stop one type of pain by inflicting a stronger more outward sign of damage. Then you have to ask why? Did he want to end his personal suffering? Or, was he signaling her that he wanted her to know, she had won? I would not need to know the answers but they certainly do.

The effects of scandal on Hollywood production value is a numbers game. These two people are humans with the need to follow their individual artistry. To slant a movie industry against one side of a scandal, as if he or she is a threat, seems unnecessary. Just because no one can safely determine the larger demon in this case, doesn't  mean that Hollywood, or anyone should take sides and create more division between artists and their craft.

Here is what I would like to see happen. I am considerably unimportant, so, so what? I would like to see both humans be forced to get help. I would like to see divorce courts attempt to restore the friendship between two departing divorcees INORDER to repair their relationship BEFORE THEY CAN HAVE ANY DIVORCE SETTLEMENTS. DIVORCE IS HORRIBLE. LOSING A FRIENDSHIP OVER TIME IS THE UGLIEST EVENT IN OUR COMMON HUMANITY. 

I WISH THEM AND THEIR CLOSEST FRIENDS, HEALING. I wish them to both have the equal right to continue their artistic endeavors. That brings healing for all of us.
author: Juanita Skelton
